      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): allow short built-in tweakcn theme names in ID validator",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix the tweakcn theme ID validator to accept short built-in theme names like `claude` (6 chars), `zinc` (4 chars), and `slate` (5 chars).\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`THEME_ID_PATTERN` in `ui/src/ui/custom-theme.ts` used `{7,127}` for the character class after the first character, requiring theme IDs to be at least 8 characters. Valid built-in tweakcn themes with shorter names were rejected with \"Unsupported tweakcn link. Expected a theme share URL.\"\n\n## Fix\n\nChange `{7,127}` to `{0,127}` — allowing theme IDs as short as 1 character while keeping the 128-character upper bound.\n\n## Test\n\nAdded regression test in `custom-theme.test.ts` verifying `claude`, `zinc`, and `slate` theme IDs are accepted.\n\n## Related\n\nCloses #88987\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] DCO signed (`git commit -s`)\n- [x] Regression test added\n- [x] Single focused change\n- [x] Verified unfixed on current main\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
